# Git + push for deploy (this filename is legacy)

**An older version of this rule wrongly said “do not use Git” and “deploy only with `railway up`”. That is incorrect for Lumo 22.**

## What to do

1. **Commit and ship:** `git status` → `git add` (relevant paths) → `git commit -m "…"` → `git push` (usually **`main`**) when the user asks to commit, save, deploy, or redeploy — unless they explicitly want **`railway up`** only.
2. **Railway CLI** (`railway up --no-gitignore`): **optional** fallback or when the user explicitly requests CLI upload; **not** the default instead of Git.

## Canonical docs (same policy)

- **`.cursor/rules/railway-deploy.mdc`**
- **`.cursor/rules/git-and-railway-deploy.mdc`**
- **`AGENTS.md`**
- **`docs/RAILWAY_DEPLOY.md`**

## Cursor settings

If **Project Rules** or **User Rules** still say “never use git” or “railway up only” for this repo, **remove or replace** them so they do not contradict the files above.
